        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 20 at 2:47PM CDT by NWS Little Rock AR</headline>
        <description>At 246 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Herbine, or 10 miles southeast of Rison, moving east at 45 mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Garrett Bridge...                 Gourd...
Calhoun...                        Cornerville...
Florence...                       Tyro...
Rowell...                         Palmyra...
Rose Hill...                      Crigler...
Plantersville...                  Fresno...
Garnett...                        Cane Creek State Park...
Pansy...                          Coleman...
Star City...                      Avery...
Herbine...                        Relfs Bluff...
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Tornado Watch remains in effect until 800 PM CDT for southeastern
Arkansas.</instruction>
